Dr Okonjo-Iweala has been appointed as the Director-General of the WTO. WTO confirmed her appointment at a special meeting of the General Council, following a selection process that included eight candidates from around the world. The tweet read: “Ngozi Okonjo-Iweala from Nigeria is appointed as the next WTO Director-General. “Her term starts on the 1st of March 2021.” Dr. Okonjo-Iweala becomes the first woman and the first African to lead the WTO. 